<paragraph blockId="15.[527,857,1383,1439]" box="[574,809,1415,1439]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">
(
<figureCitation box="[582,712,1415,1439]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[144,211,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[144,1100,1140,1439]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Wings of Perilampis species. (A) amazuluana; (B) umbrina; (C) atra; (D) deemingi sp. nov.; (E) formosula; (F) incohata sp.n.; (G) tetradactyla. Notes: Aab, anterior apical band; Pab, posterior apical band; Sab, subapical band; Db, discal band; Sbb, subbasal band." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217400/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">Figures 1D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[724,758,1415,1439]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[212,280,1648,1670]" captionTargetBox="[285,1098,171,1618]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[285,1098,170,1618]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Aculeus of Perilampsis species. (A) atra; (B) deemingi sp. nov.; (C) incohata sp. nov.; (D) umbrina; (E) diademata; (F) decellei; (G) dryades; (H) pulchella; (I) furcata; (J) woodi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217404/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">3B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[769,801,1415,1439]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[144,212,1649,1671]" captionTargetBox="[187,1060,172,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-45@8.[186,1061,172,1620]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Aculeus apex of Perilampsis species. (A) atra; (B) deemingi sp. nov.; (C) incohata sp. nov.; (D) furcata; (E) woodi; (F) umbrina; (G) diademata; (H) decellei; (I) dryades; (J) pulchella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217406/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">4B</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[212,321,1488,1512]" box="[212,321,1488,1512]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">
<emphasis box="[212,321,1488,1512]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[212,1172,1527,1679]" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">
Arista pubescent; scutum with one broad transverse band; postpronotum white; scutellum white; anatergite and katatergite completely white; legs yellow with femora dark; wing, anterior apical band without subapical tooth into cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1019,1053,1602,1620]" fontSize="8" pageId="15" pageNumber="2439">4+5</subScript>
, touching discal band, posterior apical band absent, discal band reaching posterior margin; abdomen mainly shining black-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,272,167,191]" box="[144,272,167,191]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,272,167,191]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,1104,207,391]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,212,207,231]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Head.</emphasis>
Antennal segments dark brown. Arista pubescent, longest rays at most twice the width of base of arista. Frons ventral half yellow-white, dorsal part with transverse brown band along width of orbital setae, area above posterior orbital till occiput yellow-white. Two frontals, placed parallel to medial eye margin; two orbitals, placed slightly convergent with anterior orbital located more medially. Face white, dorsal third dark brown. Occiput black-brown, only margins white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,1105,431,648]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,231,431,455]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Thorax.</emphasis>
Scutum shining black-brown, more yellowish brown near transverse suture; dark dispersed pilosity, one broad transverse band with silvery pilosity and microtrichosity anteriorly of transverse suture. Postpronotum white. Anepisternum brown, with white band occupying posterodorsal part, its ventral margin reaching posteroventral corner or almost so; with pale pilosity except in posteroventral corner with few dark setulae; one anepisternal seta. Anatergite and katatergite white. Scutellum white. Subscutellum brown. Legs pale yellow, femora and anterior half of mid and hind tibiae black-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,1104,687,903]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,204,687,711]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[218,335,687,711]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="4.[144,211,1499,1521]" captionTargetBox="[144,1100,1140,1439]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figure 1. Wings of Perilampis species. (A) amazuluana; (B) umbrina; (C) atra; (D) deemingi sp. nov.; (E) formosula; (F) incohata sp.n.; (G) tetradactyla. Notes: Aab, anterior apical band; Pab, posterior apical band; Sab, subapical band; Db, discal band; Sbb, subbasal band." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217400" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217400/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Figure 1D</figureCitation>
). Wing bands brown, largely reduced. No basal spots or streaks, except for subbasal band. Anterior apical band covering cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[844,854,730,748]" fontSize="8" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">1</subScript>
completely except for small hyaline spot in apical end of cell; covering cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[752,785,762,780]" fontSize="8" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">2+3</subScript>
only partially; without subapical tooth into cell r 
<subScript attach="left" box="[412,445,794,812]" fontSize="8" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">4+5</subScript>
. Posterior apical band absent. Subapical band strongly reduced, usually as narrow line, sometimes almost completely absent. Area between subbasal band and discal band hyaline. Discal band and anterior apical band united at pterostigma. Discal band reaching posterior wing margin. R-M ratio 0.42–0.48.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,1104,943,999]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,256,943,967]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Shining black-brown, posterior margin of tergite 2 with narrow greyish band, tergite 5 with small yellow patch posteromedially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,1104,1039,1191]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,232,1039,1063]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Female.</emphasis>
As male, except for the following characters: mid and hind tibiae dark on anterior two-thirds. Female terminalia, oviscape about two-thirds of length of abdominal tergites, shining black-brown, with black pilosity. Aculeus (
<figureCitation box="[977,1095,1103,1127]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="7.[212,280,1648,1670]" captionTargetBox="[285,1098,171,1618]" captionTargetId="figure-45@7.[285,1098,170,1618]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Figure 3. Aculeus of Perilampsis species. (A) atra; (B) deemingi sp. nov.; (C) incohata sp. nov.; (D) umbrina; (E) diademata; (F) decellei; (G) dryades; (H) pulchella; (I) furcata; (J) woodi." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217404/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
) orange, flattened, about 7 times as long as broad, apex (
<figureCitation box="[815,935,1135,1159]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="8.[144,212,1649,1671]" captionTargetBox="[187,1060,172,1616]" captionTargetId="figure-45@8.[186,1061,172,1620]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figure 4. Aculeus apex of Perilampsis species. (A) atra; (B) deemingi sp. nov.; (C) incohata sp. nov.; (D) furcata; (E) woodi; (F) umbrina; (G) diademata; (H) decellei; (I) dryades; (J) pulchella." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5217406" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5217406/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Figure 4B</figureCitation>
) strongly narrowed, pointed tip.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[144,766,1231,1255]" box="[144,766,1231,1255]" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">
<emphasis box="[144,284,1231,1255]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440">Body length.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[290,451,1231,1255]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.9" metricValueMax="4.2" metricValueMin="3.6" pageId="16" pageNumber="2440" unit="mm" value="3.9" valueMax="4.2" valueMin="3.6">3.60–4.20 mm</quantity>
